Receive Damage is the function that allows living creatures to take damage.
The function is defined as:

varargs int receive_damage(int iAmount, int ibDamType, int iAbsorbFlag,
  object oFrom, status iNoExp, status tFromPlayer)

iAmount is an int defining the amount of damage taken by the target.

ibDamType defines the weapon type being used, defined in
/secure/include/types.h

iAbsorbFlag flags are defined in /secure/include/living.h
#define AFLAG_APIERCE  1
#define AFLAG_ARMOR    2
#define AFLAG_ABSORB   3
#define AFLAG_ALL      4
  *AFLAG_APIERCE will reduce the damage the living will absorb, but does not
      negate armor altogether.
  *AFLAG_ARMOR will increase the damage the living will absorb based
      on their AC.
  *AFLAG_ABSORB will bypass AC to determine damage.
  AFLAG_ALL will return the initial iAmount bypassing resists and AC.
  *Initial damage is first reduced by any damage resists.

oFrom is the object giving the damage, or in the case of an object, should be
the holding/wearing living.

tNoExp is a 0 if the living gets experience for the damage, 1 if
  no exp is to be awarded the player.

tFromPlayer should be 0 if it's an object/room/npc, or 1 if the
  damage is being done by another player.

receive_damage() is defined in /secure/living.c
